item.description:

Identified by scraper @ 2023-07-20T21:09:15+00:00

  • Incident Date: 2023-06-20
  • City: KEASBEY
  • State: NJ
  • Report Type: A hazardous material incident
  • Mode Of Transportation: Highway
  • Carrier/Reporter: Fedex Ground Package System, Inc.
  • Hazmat Fatalities: 0
  • Hazmat Injuries: 0
  • Non-Hazmat Fatalities: 0
  • Description: SequenceEvent: During the sunrise sort, the package arrived at the hazmat cage with signs of possible internal leakage and you can hear glass moving around. Upon inspection 1 glass bottle of 4 containing "Fisher Scientific Acetonitrile" was found cracked/broken causing the internal leakage. It was then placed into a salvage drum to await further processing and to be sent back to the shipper unless otherwise. DescribePack: The Package failure was due to 1 of the 4 brown glass bottles being cracked/broken and then leaking out completely. The glass bottle seem to have cracked due to being dropped during the loading process. DurationRel: 3 and MitigateEffect: The package was opened immediately and the 1 glass bottle scraps were properly collected to avoid injury's. Then the remaining 3 glass bottles were placed into a salvage drum to await further processing.

  • Incident Date: 2023-06-15
  • City: KEASBEY
  • State: NJ
  • Report Type: A hazardous material incident
  • Mode Of Transportation: Highway
  • Carrier/Reporter: Fedex Ground Package System, Inc.
  • Hazmat Fatalities: 0
  • Hazmat Injuries: 0
  • Non-Hazmat Fatalities: 0
  • Description: SequenceEvent: During the day sort, the plastic pail arrived at the hazmat cage with some signs of possible internal leakage. Upon inspection, the pail containing "ZEP INDUSTRIAL PURPLE DEGREASER" was found with a gash/puncture at the bottom of the jerrican. The package was immediately placed into a salvage drum to await further processing from pgh. DescribePack: The package failure was due to a gash/puncture at the bottom of the plastic jerrican most likely due from loading equipment mishaps. The jerrican leaked about a quarter amount of the gallons degreaser liquid. DurationRel: 2 and MitigateEffect: The jerrican was placed upside down into a salvage drum in order to mitigate the internal leakage.

  • Description: SequenceEvent: IT APPEARS THE SHIPMENT WAS REMOVED FROM THE SYSTEM FLOW, DUE TO THE EXTERNAL CARTON BEING TORN AND WET DURING THE DAY SORT. DescribePack: UPON INSPECTION OF INNER CONTENTS DURING THE TWILIGHT SHIFT 4X5 LITERS (PLASTIC BOTTLES) RAPICIDE PA PART A AND PART B BOTTLES. ONE OUT OF THE TWO BOTTLES OF PART B HAD A LOOSE CAP WHICH CAUSED LEAKAGING ALLOWING 100% SPILLAGE. WHICH ALSO CAUSED DAMAGE TO THE OUTER PACKAGING AS WELL. DurationRel: 12 and MitigateEffect: FACILITY PROCEDURES FOR DAMAGED HAZARDOUS MATERIAL FOLLOWED, CONTENTS CONTAINED AND AWAITING DISPOSITION.
